The paper deals with coding theory and information theory, which are typically categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper specifically focuses on Reed Muller codes, which are a type of error-correcting code, and their decoding thresholds on binary memoryless symmetric channels. This falls under the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity), which deals with the design and analysis of algorithms and codes. The paper also involves a careful analysis of the weight distribution of RM codes, which could potentially fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the capacity-achieving properties of RM codes, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
